The issue here is that although the logical expression (score > threshold) 
evaluates as false, the program does not handle this case correctly. For Tu
Tundra to return "pass", it should print "review". So, we need to reverse t
the condition in the if-else statement from else {print("pass")} to {print(
{print("review")}.

Here is your corrected code:

```tundra
val score = 72;
val threshold = 80;<｜begin▁of▁sentence｜>

if (score > threshold) 
{
  print("review");
} 
else 
{
  print("pass");
}
```
